19
00:00:18,731 --> 00:00:20,024
<i>Homeward bound.</i>

20
00:00:20,107 --> 00:00:22,777
<i>On a peaceful relief mission
to the planet Aleen,</i>

21
00:00:22,860 --> 00:00:24,946
<i>R2-D2 and C-3PO</i>

22
00:00:25,112 --> 00:00:28,616
<i>were caught up in an adventure
beyond their comprehension.</i>

23
00:00:29,283 --> 00:00:31,118
<i>After finally resolving the crisis</i>

24
00:00:31,244 --> 00:00:34,121
<i>and being taken
to Jedi Master Adi Gallia's cruiser,</i>

25
00:00:34,455 --> 00:00:37,291
<i>they now head home
toward the safety of the Republic,</i>

26
00:00:37,375 --> 00:00:39,544
<i>hoping to avoid a Separatist attack.</i>

27
00:00:40,169 --> 00:00:41,587
And Mistress Padmé,

28
00:00:41,671 --> 00:00:43,005
you would not believe

29
00:00:43,089 --> 00:00:46,801
the adventures Artoo and I had
on that troubled planet of Aleen.

30
00:00:46,884 --> 00:00:49,345
We have been
in the most absurd situations.

31
00:00:49,428 --> 00:00:50,888
I could never compute.

32
00:00:50,972 --> 00:00:54,350
<i>Well, I told you, Threepio,
it's a big universe out there,</i>

33
00:00:54,433 --> 00:00:56,435
<i>beyond the few million planets you know.</i>

34
00:00:56,852 --> 00:01:00,690
And obviously, for the most part,
quite uncivilized.

35
00:01:00,773 --> 00:01:03,818
I hope never to end up on a mission
of that nature again.

36
00:01:03,985 --> 00:01:07,780
<i>Good. I need you here
to supervise the senatorial banquet.</i>

37
00:01:07,822 --> 00:01:10,283
<i>It was pushed up
and is only two days away.</i>

38
00:01:10,324 --> 00:01:12,326
Oh, my!

39
00:01:22,670 --> 00:01:25,923
They've hit the main reactor,
prepare to evacuate.

40
00:01:27,508 --> 00:01:30,052
<i>Non-essential personnel
evacuate immediately.</i>

41
00:01:30,136 --> 00:01:32,138
<i>Non-essential personnel
evacuate immediately.</i>

42
00:01:32,430 --> 00:01:33,598
Did you hear that?

43
00:01:33,806 --> 00:01:36,100
We've got to get out of here.

44
00:01:43,566 --> 00:01:44,859
It's General Grievous!

45
00:01:48,696 --> 00:01:50,448
Artoo, where are you going?

46
00:01:52,491 --> 00:01:54,118
We need to find an escape pod.

47
00:01:54,869 --> 00:01:58,789
<i>All pilots to your stations.
All flight crews, man your stations.</i>

48
00:02:03,628 --> 00:02:04,712
<i>Move to your stations!</i>

49
00:02:04,795 --> 00:02:06,797
<i>All flight crews, man your stations.</i>

50
00:02:12,470 --> 00:02:15,056
R2-D2, get down from there at once.

51
00:02:15,139 --> 00:02:16,891
This is not an escape pod.

52
00:02:17,391 --> 00:02:20,686
Well, if there's nothing better, I suppose,
it will just have to do.

53
00:02:21,812 --> 00:02:25,274
I'm sure I will live to...

54
00:02:35,451 --> 00:02:39,538
Artoo, you should know I have
total confidence in your skills as a pilot,

55
00:02:39,580 --> 00:02:42,416
provided you can avoid these star cruisers.
Oh, my!

56
00:02:47,171 --> 00:02:49,048
Avoid them the other way!

57
00:02:56,889 --> 00:02:59,809
Artoo, do something ! Get us out of here!

58
00:03:13,948 --> 00:03:14,949
They're right behind us!

59
00:03:18,536 --> 00:03:19,787
We've been hit! Ah!

60
00:03:38,264 --> 00:03:40,224
Right on target! Well done, Artoo.

61
00:03:42,727 --> 00:03:46,439
Oh, no! The reactor was hit,
it's shutting down.

62
00:03:46,480 --> 00:03:48,566
We'll disintegrate for sure.

63
00:04:05,875 --> 00:04:08,502
Fixable? This scrap pile?

64
00:04:09,044 --> 00:04:12,006
Without the tools,
this ship is utterly useless!

65
00:04:12,047 --> 00:04:15,134
I suppose, we could get out
and have a look around.

66
00:04:19,722 --> 00:04:22,808
Oh, really. You see, not even a ladder.

67
00:04:22,850 --> 00:04:24,351
Utterly useless! Utterly!

68
00:04:26,187 --> 00:04:27,813
Look, look! Over there!

69
00:04:27,855 --> 00:04:30,024
-Intruders!
-Oh!

70
00:04:30,191 --> 00:04:31,817
-Shiny!
-It's shiny!

71
00:04:31,859 --> 00:04:32,860
Intruders!

72
00:04:32,943 --> 00:04:34,653
Did you hear that?

73
00:04:43,370 --> 00:04:45,831
Whoever you are,
please note that my counterpart here

74
00:04:45,873 --> 00:04:48,876
is programmed
in 47 schools of self-defense.

75
00:04:58,469 --> 00:05:00,179
There, I've frightened them off.

76
00:05:10,606 --> 00:05:13,067
Fear not, Artoo, just little creatures.

77
00:05:13,150 --> 00:05:14,735
Can't possibly damage us!

78
00:05:15,402 --> 00:05:17,404
Oh ! Oh ! Oh!

79
00:05:32,837 --> 00:05:35,464
Get the Big Hay-Zu. He'll know what to do.

80
00:05:38,551 --> 00:05:39,635
Really!

81
00:05:40,511 --> 00:05:46,308
May I say that this is no way
to treat a friendly visitor to your planet.

82
00:05:46,892 --> 00:05:50,604
The Big Hay-Zu says
there are no friendly visitors.

83
00:05:51,021 --> 00:05:53,274
This Hay-Zu doesn't sound very reasonable.

84
00:05:53,774 --> 00:05:58,696
We do what he says, whatever he says,
for our own good.

85
00:05:59,196 --> 00:06:00,990
Your own good?

86
00:06:03,784 --> 00:06:08,330
He sends our children to fight his wars,
the lucky ones.

87
00:06:08,831 --> 00:06:11,125
What does he do to the unlucky ones?

88
00:06:27,099 --> 00:06:29,768
So, you are the intruders?

89
00:06:29,894 --> 00:06:34,231
Intruders? Oh, hardly,
Your Worshipful-ness! We are...

90
00:06:34,315 --> 00:06:38,569
On this planet,
things are what Hay-Zu says they are!

91
00:06:40,154 --> 00:06:41,155
Quiet, Artoo.

92
00:06:41,488 --> 00:06:45,951
What's this? Your friend challenges
Big Hay-Zu's authority!

93
00:06:46,035 --> 00:06:50,164
Sir, my disagreeable friend here
means no disrespect.

94
00:06:50,497 --> 00:06:53,918
We are just trying
to get back to our home planet,

95
00:06:54,001 --> 00:06:55,586
but our ship is damaged.

96
00:06:55,669 --> 00:06:57,421
And I fear, repaired or not,

97
00:06:57,504 --> 00:07:01,675
that further travel in it might not result
in our arrival there unscathed.

98
00:07:01,967 --> 00:07:04,178
That's the chance you'll have to take.

99
00:07:04,219 --> 00:07:06,680
Now get off my planet
while I'm in a good mood,

100
00:07:06,764 --> 00:07:09,516
or I'll have you dismembered
and sold for scrap.

101
00:07:09,558 --> 00:07:10,559
Free them!

102
00:07:23,697 --> 00:07:27,117
Ah, big talk for a small droid!

103
00:07:27,284 --> 00:07:29,244
Artoo, have your sensors frozen?

104
00:07:29,328 --> 00:07:32,081
I am not going to let you at him!

105
00:07:32,164 --> 00:07:36,710
In fact, I'm going to switch you off
before you cause an intergalactic incident.

106
00:07:39,463 --> 00:07:40,506
Oh, my!

107
00:07:45,719 --> 00:07:47,471
You just killed him.

108
00:07:48,639 --> 00:07:52,559
Dead. He's dead. The Big Hay-Zu is dead.

109
00:07:52,726 --> 00:07:57,523
You must understand this was an accident,
a terrible accident.

110
00:07:57,564 --> 00:07:59,566
He's dead ! He's dead!

111
00:07:59,608 --> 00:08:01,568
The Big Hay-Zu is dead!

112
00:08:01,986 --> 00:08:04,279
He's dead ! He's dead!

113
00:08:04,363 --> 00:08:06,073
The Big Hay-Zu is dead!

114
00:08:20,087 --> 00:08:23,757
Gold one, we have a proposition.

115
00:08:24,216 --> 00:08:27,011
We wish you not to leave,
but for you to stay,

116
00:08:27,594 --> 00:08:28,762
as our new leader.

117
00:08:30,806 --> 00:08:33,934
A lot you know,
you over-stuffed barrel of bolts.

118
00:08:33,976 --> 00:08:35,269
I could be a leader.

119
00:08:35,310 --> 00:08:37,938
I am honored by your consideration

120
00:08:38,022 --> 00:08:41,108
but you should choose a leader
from among your own.

121
00:08:41,567 --> 00:08:45,946
None of us has killed Hay-Zu.
None of us have earned the title.

122
00:08:46,113 --> 00:08:49,575
Terminating the big one
does not anoint me leader.

123
00:08:49,616 --> 00:08:51,285
You must choose.

124
00:08:51,368 --> 00:08:55,164
Now, who are the three smartest,
most intelligent,

125
00:08:55,247 --> 00:08:58,459
most understanding, most compassionate?

126
00:09:04,173 --> 00:09:08,177
You should choose a leader
from among these three.

127
00:09:08,260 --> 00:09:10,721
Who thinks he should be leader?

128
00:09:10,888 --> 00:09:12,973
- Yeah.
- Oh, yeah.

129
00:09:13,057 --> 00:09:14,433
And this young lady?

130
00:09:14,475 --> 00:09:16,101
Yeah!

131
00:09:16,477 --> 00:09:17,728
Lastly, him.

132
00:09:17,853 --> 00:09:20,814
Yeah!

133
00:09:21,065 --> 00:09:24,985
Congratulations!
You are now a democracy.

134
00:09:25,235 --> 00:09:27,780
-I got more votes than he did.
-No, you didn't!

135
00:09:27,821 --> 00:09:30,449
-Sit down ! It was me! It was me!
-I got the most votes.

136
00:09:30,491 --> 00:09:31,617
-That is not true.
-Ridiculous!

137
00:09:31,742 --> 00:09:33,827
No!

138
00:09:33,911 --> 00:09:34,995
No, it was me.

139
00:09:37,498 --> 00:09:40,000
I heartily agree. Is the ship ready?

140
00:09:41,126 --> 00:09:42,377
Then we'll just have to risk it,

141
00:09:42,461 --> 00:09:45,506
and leave them
to build their happy democracy,

142
00:09:45,589 --> 00:09:46,632
on their own.

143
00:09:47,174 --> 00:09:48,300
I got the votes!

144
00:09:48,550 --> 00:09:50,344
Down with democracy!

145
00:10:12,199 --> 00:10:16,036
Yes, I'm reading the gauges.
I have nothing to do but read gauges.

146
00:10:16,161 --> 00:10:18,539
Why? What do the gauges say?

147
00:10:20,249 --> 00:10:23,043
Running out of power?
The ship and us, too!

148
00:10:23,127 --> 00:10:26,255
Oh, I knew we should never
have left the Jedi cruiser.

149
00:10:26,505 --> 00:10:28,674
Another planet?

150
00:10:43,105 --> 00:10:45,399
According to the positional
system coordinates,

151
00:10:45,440 --> 00:10:46,984
this is Balnab,

152
00:10:47,067 --> 00:10:51,155
a stellar remnant in its emerging stages
of organic development.

153
00:10:51,822 --> 00:10:54,908
I've heard terrible stories
about these primitive planets.

154
00:10:59,872 --> 00:11:01,081
I dare not imagine

155
00:11:01,165 --> 00:11:04,251
what is beginning to swim
in their primordial soups.

156
00:11:06,128 --> 00:11:10,090
I know we have to find power.
But do we have to find it out there?

157
00:11:13,760 --> 00:11:16,805
Afraid? Of course I'm not afraid.

158
00:11:20,851 --> 00:11:21,894
I am now.

159
00:11:21,935 --> 00:11:25,606
Quickly, see if your scanners
can find a viable power source.

160
00:11:35,616 --> 00:11:37,576
Yes, me, too.

161
00:11:39,036 --> 00:11:41,121
Life forms? What kind?

162
00:11:49,880 --> 00:11:54,092
They appear to be humanoid
and completely devoid of intelligence.

163
00:11:58,555 --> 00:12:00,599
Artoo, make a dash for it!

164
00:12:11,985 --> 00:12:13,654
What are they?

165
00:12:13,737 --> 00:12:15,989
Bring them. The leader will know.

166
00:12:16,365 --> 00:12:18,158
Another leader? Oh!

167
00:12:18,242 --> 00:12:21,995
I do hope this one is more understanding.

168
00:12:29,294 --> 00:12:31,546
My fault! Ha! I should have known.

169
00:12:42,224 --> 00:12:46,019
<i>Who dares come to my land?</i>

170
00:12:47,229 --> 00:12:51,817
Just two wandering droids
searching to find their home!

171
00:12:52,317 --> 00:12:56,780
<i>Droids? What are droids?</i>

172
00:12:57,155 --> 00:13:00,492
Well, kind sir, droids are mechanical beings

173
00:13:00,575 --> 00:13:03,245
possessing artificial intelligence,
designed to make...

174
00:13:03,328 --> 00:13:05,497
<i>-Silence!</i>
-At once, sir.

175
00:13:05,539 --> 00:13:09,251
Your Sir-ness, being silent
is one of my specialties.

176
00:13:10,711 --> 00:13:16,967
<i>Who dares to bring these non-living things
before me?</i>

177
00:13:17,092 --> 00:13:20,387
It was I who brought them. I thought that...

178
00:13:23,515 --> 00:13:24,558
How unfortunate.

179
00:13:24,599 --> 00:13:29,229
<i>No one thinks here but me!</i>

180
00:13:30,856 --> 00:13:31,898
Artoo, be quiet.

181
00:13:31,940 --> 00:13:36,320
This situation calls
for my most delicate diplomatic skills.

182
00:13:36,403 --> 00:13:40,073
Please excuse my insolent friend,
Your Eminence-ness,

183
00:13:40,240 --> 00:13:42,117
but I know a holographic image...

184
00:13:42,367 --> 00:13:46,413
<i>I know not of your blasphemy.</i>

185
00:13:54,588 --> 00:13:57,591
<i>Perhaps "holographic"
is the incorrect word in your native tongue,</i>

186
00:13:57,632 --> 00:13:59,676
<i>but it is obvious that you are not real.</i>

187
00:13:59,760 --> 00:14:00,927
<i>Not real!</i>

188
00:14:01,303 --> 00:14:03,638
<i>I'll show you not real!</i>

189
00:14:10,062 --> 00:14:12,439
Hey, what are you doing back here?

190
00:14:13,106 --> 00:14:18,862
<i>I said what are you doing back here?</i>

191
00:14:19,446 --> 00:14:20,614
Back where?

192
00:14:22,532 --> 00:14:25,869
Help you? Whereabouts...

193
00:14:28,997 --> 00:14:30,457
We're not gonna help you.

194
00:14:30,499 --> 00:14:34,002
We worked hard
to keep these mindless organics enslaved.

195
00:14:34,086 --> 00:14:37,422
And if you want to order someone around,
get your own organics.

196
00:14:39,466 --> 00:14:40,467
Oh, yeah!

197
00:14:40,592 --> 00:14:45,847
And just how is an astromech unit
going to make our loyal subjects rebel?

198
00:14:57,317 --> 00:14:58,527
Uh-oh.

199
00:15:00,987 --> 00:15:02,155
Oh, my!

200
00:15:02,364 --> 00:15:04,241
Oi, get them!

201
00:15:05,826 --> 00:15:07,160
Uh-oh, again!

202
00:15:12,499 --> 00:15:13,500
Artoo!

203
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:17,170
It's time to leave
but we still need to recharge.

204
00:15:18,171 --> 00:15:20,340
Here they come! They're coming for us.

205
00:15:20,924 --> 00:15:22,551
We're done for!

206
00:15:23,343 --> 00:15:25,429
They're gonna kill us!

207
00:15:25,637 --> 00:15:27,013
Run for it!

208
00:15:45,115 --> 00:15:47,701
It's all your fault, Artoo, all your fault.

209
00:15:47,742 --> 00:15:49,703
Whatever will we do now?

210
00:15:53,832 --> 00:15:55,792
Artoo, I'm talking to you.

211
00:15:57,669 --> 00:15:58,920
Please don't mumble.

212
00:16:02,716 --> 00:16:05,927
Artoo, you're almost out of power.

213
00:16:06,011 --> 00:16:07,429
Here, rest.

214
00:16:10,557 --> 00:16:11,558
Me?

215
00:16:11,600 --> 00:16:16,646
I have 1 .723% left in my power core.

216
00:16:16,730 --> 00:16:20,066
I thought for sure you would have
figured something out by now.

217
00:16:20,108 --> 00:16:22,235
You're usually so good at that sort of thing.

218
00:16:27,240 --> 00:16:30,744
Oh, Artoo, don't leave me, please.

219
00:16:31,578 --> 00:16:33,371
Rest, my friend.

220
00:16:33,413 --> 00:16:37,667
I will be joining you soon.

221
00:17:00,232 --> 00:17:03,318
That Republic Y-wing
is a great prize.

222
00:17:03,485 --> 00:17:06,112
Do you think
there are any Jedi around?

223
00:17:06,154 --> 00:17:07,447
Don't worry.

224
00:17:07,531 --> 00:17:11,201
We be takin' off
before anyone realizes we've landed.

225
00:17:11,284 --> 00:17:13,495
What have we here?

226
00:17:13,578 --> 00:17:16,540
Looks like two droids
that ran out of power.

227
00:17:17,374 --> 00:17:20,043
Lookie, lookie here.

228
00:17:21,211 --> 00:17:22,671
Come to papa.

229
00:17:22,754 --> 00:17:24,005
There you go.

230
00:17:28,552 --> 00:17:30,011
This should be a fun one.

231
00:17:39,563 --> 00:17:43,149
Who would rescue us? Master Anakin?

232
00:17:44,734 --> 00:17:47,445
Artoo, you're recharged.

233
00:17:48,029 --> 00:17:49,656
I'm recharged!

234
00:17:49,739 --> 00:17:50,824
We survived.

235
00:17:51,283 --> 00:17:52,284
Where are we?

236
00:17:54,119 --> 00:17:55,328
Pirates?

237
00:17:58,164 --> 00:17:59,165
Oh, my.

238
00:18:10,218 --> 00:18:12,345
What are they cheering for?

239
00:18:20,061 --> 00:18:22,188
Oh, goodness gracious me!

240
00:18:22,814 --> 00:18:24,733
Soon it will be us.

241
00:18:36,161 --> 00:18:37,203
Oh, my stars!

242
00:18:39,331 --> 00:18:40,332
Oh, no!

243
00:18:45,211 --> 00:18:49,132
General, we've come across
what appears to be a pirate ship.

244
00:18:49,591 --> 00:18:54,137
Use that ship for target practice. Open fire!

245
00:18:54,721 --> 00:18:58,058
All forward cannons open fire.
Battle stations!

246
00:19:03,980 --> 00:19:04,981
Oh, my!

247
00:19:06,399 --> 00:19:07,817
Go get him, Artoo.

248
00:19:25,210 --> 00:19:28,880
Oh, no, we'll never get back to the ship!

249
00:19:39,933 --> 00:19:41,017
We surrender.

250
00:19:41,101 --> 00:19:42,185
We surrender!

251
00:19:43,520 --> 00:19:44,854
Uh, where did you come from?

252
00:19:45,397 --> 00:19:46,940
They must be pirate droids.

253
00:19:47,273 --> 00:19:48,775
Pirate droids!

254
00:19:48,817 --> 00:19:49,818
You're under arrest.

255
00:19:50,276 --> 00:19:52,237
Pirate droids? We're not pirate droids.

256
00:19:52,278 --> 00:19:53,947
We are part of the Republic.

257
00:19:54,989 --> 00:19:56,950
Oh, yes, we are pirate droids.

258
00:19:57,409 --> 00:19:58,993
That is what we thought.

259
00:19:59,077 --> 00:20:03,081
Send them off to the incinerator room
with the rest of the pirate scum.

260
00:20:03,498 --> 00:20:05,166
The incinerator room?

261
00:20:05,625 --> 00:20:11,464
Yes. You will be melted down
for General Grievous' war machine.

262
00:20:16,386 --> 00:20:18,054
This is terrible.

263
00:20:24,811 --> 00:20:26,312
No! No!

264
00:21:00,013 --> 00:21:03,558
Oh, this trip has been nothing but
calamity all the way.

265
00:21:06,603 --> 00:21:09,397
Thanks for the rescue, Master Plo.

266
00:21:12,442 --> 00:21:14,194
General Grievous has fled.

267
00:21:14,277 --> 00:21:17,280
Very good ! Finish off the remaining droids.

268
00:21:17,363 --> 00:21:18,740
We're Republic.

269
00:21:19,032 --> 00:21:22,494
We belong to Senator Amidala.
Don't shoot. Don't shoot!

270
00:21:22,827 --> 00:21:24,829
I can't believe it.

271
00:21:24,871 --> 00:21:27,373
You know these droids,
Commander Wolff e?

272
00:21:27,415 --> 00:21:28,416
Yes, sir.

273
00:21:28,500 --> 00:21:30,585
We transported them
to Master Gallia's ship

274
00:21:30,668 --> 00:21:32,212
after we left the planet Aleen.

275
00:21:32,712 --> 00:21:36,508
Yes, Commander Wolff e.
How have you been, sir?

276
00:21:36,674 --> 00:21:38,843
We have been on quite an adventure.

277
00:21:39,260 --> 00:21:42,388
Well, I'm certain
Wolff e would love to hear about it.

278
00:21:42,430 --> 00:21:44,140
Uh, actually, sir...

279
00:21:44,516 --> 00:21:47,393
-Excellent! It's a long story.
-Uh...

280
00:21:47,435 --> 00:21:49,854
- And you won't believe it.
- Sir, excuse me...

281
00:21:50,063 --> 00:21:51,856
I hardly believe it myself.

282
00:21:52,023 --> 00:21:53,733
It all started when...

283
00:21:53,757 --> 00:21:58,757
http://hiqve.com/

